Knights are heavy melee fighters trained in formation discipline and coordinated aggression.
They descend from the warden tradition, formalized during the Iron Reformation after the Ninth Meridian Catastrophe.
The Compact of the Seven Chains established shared doctrine and a new officer class loyal to principles over employers.
Core doctrine: controlled aggression within disciplined structure reliably defeats unstructured individual excellence.
Combat role is frontline melee with emphasis on sustained pressure, defense, and formation coordination.
Training occurs in formal academies that replaced the earlier Compact-era mentorship model.
The motto encodes three commitments: break the line, hold the ground, leave no fallen comrade behind.
Knights contrast with Swordsmen, who emphasize individual blade mastery over group tactics.
The Crusader class synthesizes Knight formation doctrine with Swordsman individual techniques.
